Queries

get_run

Description

fetch data from the table: "simpipe.runs" using primary key columns

Response

Returns a runs

Arguments
Name Description
run_id - uuid!

Example

Query
query Get_run($run_id: uuid!) {
  get_run(run_id: $run_id) {
    created
    ended
    env_list
    name
    run_id
    simulation {
      created
      model_id
      name
      pipeline_description
      runs {
        ...runsFragment
      }
      runs_aggregate {
        ...runs_aggregateFragment
      }
      simulation_id
      userid
    }
    simulation_id
    started
    status
    steps {
      created
      ended
      env_variables {
        ...simpipe_env_variableFragment
      }
      env_variables_aggregate {
        ...simpipe_env_variable_aggregateFragment
      }
      image
      log {
        ...simpipe_logsFragment
      }
      name
      pipeline_step_number
      resource_usages {
        ...simpipe_resource_usageFragment
      }
      resource_usages_aggregate {
        ...simpipe_resource_usage_aggregateFragment
      }
      run_id
      started
      status
      step_id
    }
    steps_aggregate {
      aggregate {
        ...steps_aggregate_fieldsFragment
      }
      nodes {
        ...stepsFragment
      }
    }
    timeout_value
    userid
  }
}
Variables
{"run_id": uuid}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "get_run": {
      "created": timestamptz,
      "ended": timestamptz,
      "env_list": jsonb,
      "name": "abc123",
      "run_id": uuid,
      "simulation": simulations,
      "simulation_id": uuid,
      "started": timestamptz,
      "status": "active",
      "steps": [steps],
      "steps_aggregate": steps_aggregate,
      "timeout_value": 123,
      "userid": "abc123"
    }
  }
}

Queries

simulations

Description

fetch data from the table: "simpipe.simulations"

Response

Returns [simulations!]!

Arguments
Name Description
distinct_on - [simulations_select_column!] distinct select on columns
limit - Int limit the number of rows returned
offset - Int skip the first n rows. Use only with order_by
order_by - [simulations_order_by!] sort the rows by one or more columns
where - simulations_bool_exp filter the rows returned

Example

Query
query Simulations(
  $distinct_on: [simulations_select_column!],
  $limit: Int,
  $offset: Int,
  $order_by: [simulations_order_by!],
  $where: simulations_bool_exp
) {
  simulations(
    distinct_on: $distinct_on,
    limit: $limit,
    offset: $offset,
    order_by: $order_by,
    where: $where
  ) {
    created
    model_id
    name
    pipeline_description
    runs {
      created

steps_aggregate

Description

fetch aggregated fields from the table: "simpipe.steps"

Response

Returns a steps_aggregate!

Arguments
Name Description
distinct_on - [steps_select_column!] distinct select on columns
limit - Int limit the number of rows returned
offset - Int skip the first n rows. Use only with order_by
order_by - [steps_order_by!] sort the rows by one or more columns
where - steps_bool_exp filter the rows returned

Example

Query
subscription Steps_aggregate(
  $distinct_on: [steps_select_column!],
  $limit: Int,
  $offset: Int,
  $order_by: [steps_order_by!],
  $where: steps_bool_exp
) {
  steps_aggregate(
    distinct_on: $distinct_on,
    limit: $limit,
    offset: $offset,
    order_by: $order_by,
    where: $where
  ) {
    aggregate {
      avg {
        ...steps_avg_fieldsFragment
      }
      count
      max {
        ...steps_max_fieldsFragment
      }
      min {
        ...steps_min_fieldsFragment
      }
      stddev {
        ...steps_stddev_fieldsFragment
      }
      stddev_pop {
        ...steps_stddev_pop_fieldsFragment
      }
      stddev_samp {
        ...steps_stddev_samp_fieldsFragment
      }
      sum {
        ...steps_sum_fieldsFragment
      }
      var_pop {
        ...steps_var_pop_fieldsFragment
      }
      var_samp {
        ...steps_var_samp_fieldsFragment
      }
      variance {
        ...steps_variance_fieldsFragment
      }
    }
    nodes {
      created
      ended
      env_variables {
        ...simpipe_env_variableFragment
      }
      env_variables_aggregate {
        ...simpipe_env_variable_aggregateFragment
      }
      image
      log {
        ...simpipe_logsFragment
      }
      name
      pipeline_step_number
      resource_usages {
        ...simpipe_resource_usageFragment
      }
      resource_usages_aggregate {
        ...simpipe_resource_usage_aggregateFragment
      }
      run_id
      started
      status
      step_id
    }
  }
}
